author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high (or #oven{} to 500 degrees). Bring
a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Halve @Heirloom Grape Tomatoes{10%oz} lengthwise.
Cut @Fresh Mozzarella{4%oz} into small cubes.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together mozzarella and @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high
heat (use an ovenproof pan if you have one). Add tomatoes and cook, tossing,
until they start to burst, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove pan from heat and add
@Spinach{5%oz}. Set aside.

Once water is boiling, add @Spinach and Artichoke Ravioli{18%oz} to pot. Cook
until al dente, ~{4-5%minutes}. Carefully scoop out and reserve ¼ cup ravioli
cooking water, then drain.

Transfer ravioli to pan with tomatoes and spinach. Return pan to medium heat.
Add @Pesto{4%oz}, reserved ravioli cooking water, and @Sour Cream{6%tbsp}. Stir
gently until spinach wilts and a creamy sauce forms, about ~{2%minutes}. Season
with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture to a medium #baking dish{} at
> this point.

Sprinkle ravioli with panko crust mixture. Broil (or bake) until panko is
golden brown and cheese melts, ~{3-5%minutes}. Divide between plates and serve.

> This recipe features the flavors of everyone's favorite party dip stuffed into
> a pasta shell with fresh veggies and a creamy pesto sauce that makes them
> absolutely irresistible.